'''Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine''' (おおさかやまぐちじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in Anamushi, {{jalink|Kashiba City|Q696643}}, {{jalink|Nara Prefecture|Q131287}}.

=== Overview ===
It is enshrined southwest of {{jalink|Futakami Station|Q7034597}} on the {{jalink|Kintetsu Osaka Line|Q1052545}}.

Together with {{jalink|Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine (Kashiba City Ōsaka)|Q135069036|Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine}} in the Ōsaka district, it is identified as the shrine that enshrined the Ōsaka deity mentioned in the dream oracle recorded in the 9th year of {{jalink|Emperor Sujin|Q333530}} in the '{{jalink|Kojiki|Q813031}}' and '{{jalink|Nihon Shoki|Q813935}}': “With eight red shields and eight red spears, enshrine the god of Sumisaka; with eight black shields and eight black spears, enshrine the god of Ōsaka.” (Incidentally, the god of Sumisaka is identified with {{jalink|Sumisaka Shrine (Uda City)||Sumisaka Shrine}} in {{jalink|Uda City|Q863747}}.)<ref name="city-muse">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/1655.pdf Ōsaka / Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine] - Kashiba City Futakami Mountain Museum</ref><ref name="pref-db">[https://www.pref.nara.jp/miryoku/ikasu-nara/bunkashigen/main00217.html Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, deity statues, and treasure items (Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine deity statues and treasure items)] - Nara Prefecture Historical and Cultural Resources Database</ref>.

In addition, together with the Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine in the Ōsaka district, it is one of the candidate shrines (ronsha) for Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine, which is one of the {{jalink|List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|Q11433427|Shikinaisha of Yamato Province}}.<ref name="city-muse"/><ref name="pref-db"/><ref name="city">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/soshiki/15/4951.html Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine (Anamushi)] - Kashiba City</ref>.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{jalink|Ōyamatsumi-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Susanoo-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto}}

